# Sūra XCIII.: <u>Dh</u>uhā, or The Glorious Morning Light.

### Section 1

![](../gif/093/093_001.gif)

1. Wa**al**<u>dd</u>u<u>ha</u>

1\. By the Glorious  
Morning Light,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_002.gif)

2. Wa**a**llayli i<u>tha</u> saj<u>a</u>

2\. And by the Night  
When it is still,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_003.gif)

3. M<u>a</u> waddaAAaka rabbuka wam<u>a</u> qal<u>a</u>

3\. Thy Guardian-Lord  
Hath not forsaken thee,  
Nor is He displeased,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_004.gif)

4. Walal-<u>a</u>khiratu khayrun laka mina al-ool<u>a</u>

4\. And verily the hereafter  
Will be better for thee  
Than the present.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_005.gif)

5. Walasawfa yuAA<u>t</u>eeka rabbuka fatar<u>da</u>

5\. And soon will thy  
Guardian-Lord give thee  
(That wherewith) thou  
Shalt be well-pleased.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_006.gif)

6. Alam yajidka yateeman fa<u>a</u>w<u>a</u>

6\. Did He not find thee  
An orphan and give thee  
Shelter (and care)?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_007.gif)

7. Wawajadaka <u>da</u>llan fahad<u>a</u>

7\. And He found thee  
Wandering, and He gave  
Thee guidance.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_008.gif)

8. Wawajadaka AA<u>a</u>-ilan faaghn<u>a</u>

8\. And He found thee  
In need, and made  
Thee independent.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_009.gif)

9. Faamm<u>a</u> alyateema fal<u>a</u> taqhar

9\. Therefore, treat not  
The orphan with harshness,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_010.gif)

10. Waamm<u>a</u> a**l**ss<u>a</u>-ila fal<u>a</u> tanhar

10\. Nor repulse the petitioner  
(Unheard);

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/093/093_011.gif)

11. Waamm<u>a</u> biniAAmati rabbika fa<u>h</u>addith  

11\. But the Bounty  
Of thy Lord—  
Rehearse and proclaim!

